  "_metadata": {
    "model": "claude-fable-5",
    "cost_usd": 0.18806375,
    "duration_s": 54.921
  },
  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "ls && cat stm32-project.jsonc 2>/dev/null || cat ../stm32-project.jsonc 2>/dev/null",
        "description": "Check for project descriptor to learn device family"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral SPI1",
        "description": "Read SPI1 registers (SVD-decoded) to check RXDMAEN/SPE"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 prog list-probes",
        "description": "List attached ST-LINK probes"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral SPI1",
        "description": "Read SPI1 registers on the L476RG probe"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral RCC 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor rn in ('AHB1ENR','APB2ENR'):\n    r=d['registers'][rn]\n    print(rn, hex(r['raw_value']), {k:v['raw_value'] for k,v in r['fields'].items() if v['raw_value']})\n\"",
        "description": "Read RCC clock-enable registers for SPI1/DMA1"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "**No \u2014 neither SPI1 nor DMA is even clocked on this target.**\n\nRead live (attach without reset, halted in place) on the NUCLEO-L476RG (probe `066DFF\u2026`, selected explicitly since the N6570-DK is also on the bench):\n\n| Check | Register | Value | Verdict |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| SPI1 clock | `RCC.APB2ENR` | `0x0` (SPI1EN = 0) | SPI1 unclocked \u2014 its registers read as zeros |\n| DMA1/DMA2 clocks | `RCC.AHB1ENR` | `0x100` (only FLASHEN) | DMA1EN = 0, DMA2EN = 0 \u2014 no DMA controller running |\n| SPI1 RX-DMA request | `SPI1.CR2.RXDMAEN` | 0 | Not requesting DMA |\n| SPI1 enabled | `SPI1.CR1.SPE` | 0 | Peripheral disabled |\n\nThe telltale: `SPI1.CR2` read raw `0x0`, but its hardware reset value on the L4 is `0x0700` (DS = 8-bit). An all-zero readback below reset value means the bus clock is gated, which RCC confirms.\n\nSo the answer chain is: DMA1 Ch2 / DMA2 Ch3 (the L4's SPI1_RX routes) can't be armed because no DMA controller is clocked, and SPI1 itself was never initialized. That's consistent with this being the **BLINKY** firmware from the F-PROJ descriptor \u2014 GPIO-only, no SPI/DMA init in `main()`. If you expected SPI+DMA firmware, the wrong image is on the board."
}